{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SourceFuncsProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running the idle function)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" call doesn’t block too long","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and miss the next timeout."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"since it must wait until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" has been called before it knows whether","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"any events need to be processed. It sets the returned timeout to -1 to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"indicate that it doesn’t mind how long the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call blocks. In the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"check function, it tests the results of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call to see if the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"required condition has been met, and returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if so."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"SourceFuncsProtocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsProtocol"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19SourceFuncsProtocolP","symbolKind":"protocol"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/check","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/dispatch","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/finalize","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/prepare"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"inheritsFrom"},{"type":"conformingTypes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"],"title":"Conforming Types","kind":"relationships"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","title":"MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/prepare":{"title":"prepare","abstract":[{"text":"Called before all the file descriptors are polled. If","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the source can determine that it is ready here (without waiting for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call) it should return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":". It can also return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"code":"timeout_","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value which should be the maximum timeout (in milliseconds)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"which should be passed to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" call. The actual timeout used will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be -1 if all sources returned -1, or it will be the minimum of all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"code":"timeout_","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values returned which were >= 0.  Since 2.36 this may","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", in which case the effect is as if the function always returns","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" with a timeout of -1.  If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"prepare"},{"text":" returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"timeout and the source also has a ready time set, then the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lower of the two will be used.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/prepare","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"prepare","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GSourceFuncsPrepareFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsPrepareFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/prepare"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/finalize":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Called when the source is finalized. At this point,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the source will have been destroyed, had its callback cleared, and have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"been removed from its [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"], but it will still have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its final reference count, so methods can be called on it from within"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this function. This may be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", in which case the effect is as if the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function does nothing and returns.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/finalize","role":"symbol","title":"finalize","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/finalize","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"finalize","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsFinalizeFunc","text":"GSourceFuncsFinalizeFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/sourceRemove":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceremove","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this macro as the return value of a [callback"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFunc"},{"text":"] to remove","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source"},{"type":"text","text":"] from the main loop."}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sourceRemove","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int32","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V"}],"title":"sourceRemove","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PointerWrapper":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Protocol for GLib types that wrap pointers."}],"title":"PointerWrapper","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pointerwrapper","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/sourceremovebyfuncs(userdata:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sourceRemoveByFuncs","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Removes a source from the default main loop context given the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source functions and user data.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol":{"title":"SourceFuncsProtocol","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"text":" struct contains a table of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SourceFuncsProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","title":"SourceFuncsRef","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsref"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/dispatch":{"title":"dispatch","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/dispatch","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/dispatch","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"dispatch"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsDispatchFunc","text":"GSourceFuncsDispatchFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Called to dispatch the event source, after it has returned"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" in either its ","type":"text"},{"code":"prepare","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"check"},{"type":"text","text":" function, or if a ready time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has been reached. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"dispatch","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function receives a callback function and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"user data. The callback function may be "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if the source was never"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"connected to a callback using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.set_callback"},{"text":"]. The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dispatch"},{"text":" function should call the callback function with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"user_data"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whatever additional parameters are needed for this type of event source."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The return value of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dispatch"},{"text":" function should be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[const","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] if the source should be removed or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[const","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceContinue","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] to keep it."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncs":{"title":"SourceFuncs","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncs","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncs","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"text":" struct contains a table of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncs"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/sourceContinue":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this macro as the return value of a [callback"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFunc","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] to leave"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true},{"text":"] in the main loop.","type":"text"}],"title":"sourceContinue","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcecontinue","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sourceContinue"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gboolean","text":"gboolean"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceContinue"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/check":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/check","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Called after all the file descriptors are polled. The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source should return ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if it is ready to be dispatched. Note that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some time may have passed since the previous prepare function was called,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"so the source should be checked again here.  Since 2.36 this may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", in which case the effect is as if the function always returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"check","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFuncsCheckFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsCheckFunc"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/check","kind":"symbol","title":"check"}}}